The phone evidence:

Lisanne's phone died at the exact time that all the 77 failed login attempts began to occur on Kris' phone. The most likely explanation is that Lisanne had both phones and when her own phone died she began using Kris'. Not knowing the password, resulted in all the failed attempts. She kept trying to get in and was guessing things it could be (her friend's birthday etc).

There's really no good explanation for an abductor/murderer to care about getting into the phone and if anything, accessing the phone just adds additional evidence due to pings. An abductor/murderer would much more likely want to get rid of the phones ASAP and dump them in a deep hole or water body where they'd never be found.

Now as to why Lisanne would have both phones: there are a number of reasons: Kris had already died, Kris became ill and couldn't move or talk, one was injured and the other went for help (either the injured or the helper held onto both phones to use the light or call for help if one phone got signal), they were running from someone and the phones were in the backpack and the two somehow got separated with the one with the backpack having both phones, etc.

I'm curious to know where the ping signal was on the one successful connection was to emergency services that lasted 2 seconds. If it was on the jungle trail, that would eliminate the water hole theory I think. Unless the claim is the girls were killed near the water hole and then the killer took the phones back to the jungle (but then how would the killer have the passwords to get in and then no longer have the passwords later on).
